{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":844,"text":"As a kid, I used to dream about the ocean."},{"time":3461,"text":"It was this wild place\nfull of color and life,"},{"time":7812,"text":"home to these alien-looking,\nfantastical creatures."},{"time":11056,"text":"I pictured big sharks\nruling the food chain"},{"time":13498,"text":"and saw graceful sea turtles\ndancing across coral reefs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":16726,"text":"As a marine biologist turned photographer,"},{"time":18765,"text":"I've spent most of my career\nlooking for places"},{"time":21609,"text":"as magical as those I used\nto dream about when I was little."},{"time":25479,"text":"As you can see,"},{"time":26654,"text":"I began exploring bodies of water\nat a fairly young age."},{"time":29304,"text":"But the first time\nI truly went underwater,"},{"time":31344,"text":"I was about 10 years old."},{"time":32769,"text":"And I can still vividly remember\nfuriously finning"},{"time":35440,"text":"to reach this old, encrusted\ncannon on a shallow coral reef."},{"time":38939,"text":"And when I finally managed\nto grab hold of it,"},{"time":41131,"text":"I looked up, and I was instantly\nsurrounded by fish"},{"time":44240,"text":"in all colors of the rainbow."},{"time":46213,"text":"That was the day\nI fell in love with the ocean."}]},{"cues":[{"time":48840,"text":"Thomas Peschak"}]},{"cues":[{"time":50229,"text":"Conservation Photographer"}]},{"cues":[{"time":52991,"text":"In my 40 years on this planet,"},{"time":54665,"text":"I've had the great privilege to explore"},{"time":56547,"text":"some of its most incredible seascapes"},{"time":58659,"text":"for National Geographic Magazine"},{"time":60671,"text":"and the Save Our Seas Foundation."},{"time":62322,"text":"I've photographed everything\nfrom really, really big sharks"},{"time":65462,"text":"to dainty ones that fit\nin the palm of your hand."},{"time":68679,"text":"I've smelled the fishy, fishy breath\nof humpback whales"},{"time":71655,"text":"feeding just feet away from me"},{"time":73290,"text":"in the cold seas off Canada's\nGreat Bear Rainforest."},{"time":76138,"text":"And I've been privy to the mating rituals\nof green sea turtles"},{"time":79099,"text":"in the Mozambique Channel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":80461,"text":"Everyone on this planet affects\nand is affected by the ocean."},{"time":84209,"text":"And the pristine seas\nI used to dream of as a child"},{"time":86986,"text":"are becoming harder and harder to find."},{"time":89702,"text":"They are becoming more compressed"},{"time":91821,"text":"and more threatened."},{"time":93691,"text":"As we humans continue to maintain our role"},{"time":96269,"text":"as the leading predator on earth,"},{"time":98634,"text":"I've witnessed and photographed\nmany of these ripple effects firsthand."},{"time":103077,"text":"For a long time, I thought\nI had to shock my audience"},{"time":106273,"text":"out of their indifference\nwith disturbing images."},{"time":108606,"text":"And while this approach has merits,"},{"time":110530,"text":"I have come full circle."},{"time":112368,"text":"I believe that the best way\nfor me to effect change"},{"time":115011,"text":"is to sell love."},{"time":116632,"text":"I guess I'm a matchmaker of sorts"},{"time":118703,"text":"and as a photographer,"},{"time":120212,"text":"I have the rare opportunity"},{"time":122046,"text":"to reveal animals and entire ecosystems"},{"time":124392,"text":"that lie hidden beneath\nthe ocean's surface."},{"time":127457,"text":"You can't love something\nand become a champion for it"},{"time":130266,"text":"if you don't know it exists."},{"time":132425,"text":"Uncovering this -- that is the power\nof conservation photography."}]},{"cues":[{"time":137154,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":140561,"text":"I've visited hundreds of marine locations,"},{"time":143385,"text":"but there are a handful of seascapes"},{"time":145335,"text":"that have touched me incredibly deeply."},{"time":148928,"text":"The first time I experienced\nthat kind of high"},{"time":151670,"text":"was about 10 years ago,"},{"time":153087,"text":"off South Africa's rugged, wild coast."},{"time":155946,"text":"And every June and July,"},{"time":157316,"text":"enormous shoals of sardines\ntravel northwards"},{"time":159749,"text":"in a mass migration\nwe call the Sardine Run."},{"time":162098,"text":"And boy, do those fish\nhave good reason to run."},{"time":164731,"text":"In hot pursuit are hoards\nof hungry and agile predators."},{"time":169044,"text":"Common dolphins hunt together"},{"time":170926,"text":"and they can separate some\nof the sardines from the main shoal"},{"time":173871,"text":"and they create bait balls."},{"time":175299,"text":"They drive and trap the fish upward\nagainst the ocean surface"},{"time":179011,"text":"and then they rush in to dine"},{"time":180603,"text":"on this pulsating and movable feast."},{"time":183438,"text":"Close behind are sharks."},{"time":185258,"text":"Now, most people believe"},{"time":186437,"text":"that sharks and dolphins\nare these mortal enemies,"},{"time":188838,"text":"but during the Sardine Run,\nthey actually coexist."},{"time":191634,"text":"In fact, dolphins actually\nhelp sharks feed more effectively."},{"time":195829,"text":"Without dolphins, the bait balls\nare more dispersed"},{"time":199435,"text":"and sharks often end up\nwith what I call a sardine donut,"},{"time":203197,"text":"or a mouth full of water."},{"time":204681,"text":"Now, while I've had a few spicy moments\nwith sharks on the sardine run,"},{"time":208746,"text":"I know they don't see me as prey."},{"time":210836,"text":"However, I get bumped and tail-slapped\njust like any other guest"},{"time":214063,"text":"at this rowdy, rowdy banquet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":217785,"text":"From the shores of Africa we travel east,"},{"time":220738,"text":"across the vastness\nthat is the Indian Ocean"},{"time":222863,"text":"to the Maldives, an archipelago\nof coral islands."},{"time":226779,"text":"And during the stormy southwest monsoon,"},{"time":229341,"text":"manta rays from all across the archipelago"},{"time":231675,"text":"travel to a tiny speck\nin Baa Atoll called Hanifaru."},{"time":234952,"text":"Armies of crustaceans,"},{"time":236159,"text":"most no bigger than the size\nof your pupils,"},{"time":238397,"text":"are the mainstay of the manta ray's diet."},{"time":242185,"text":"When plankton concentrations\nbecome patchy,"},{"time":244992,"text":"manta rays feed alone"},{"time":246202,"text":"and they somersault themselves\nbackwards again and again,"},{"time":248938,"text":"very much like a puppy\nchasing its own tail."}]},{"cues":[{"time":251757,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":255011,"text":"However, when plankton densities increase,"},{"time":257528,"text":"the mantas line up head-to-tail\nto form these long feeding chains,"},{"time":261751,"text":"and any tasty morsel that escapes\nthe first or second manta in line"},{"time":265099,"text":"is surely to be gobbled up\nby the next or the one after."},{"time":269912,"text":"As plankton levels peak in the bay,"},{"time":271832,"text":"the mantas swim closer and closer together"},{"time":274061,"text":"in a unique behavior\nwe call cyclone feeding."},{"time":276852,"text":"And as they swirl in tight formation,"},{"time":279146,"text":"this multi-step column of mantas"},{"time":280841,"text":"creates its own vortex, sucking in\nand delivering the plankton"},{"time":284742,"text":"right into the mantas' cavernous mouths."},{"time":287574,"text":"The experience of diving\namongst such masses of hundreds of rays"},{"time":291940,"text":"is truly unforgettable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":294881,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":342248,"text":"When I first photographed Hanifaru,"},{"time":343953,"text":"the site enjoyed no protection"},{"time":345539,"text":"and was threatened by development."},{"time":347186,"text":"And working with NGOs\nlike the Manta Trust,"},{"time":349313,"text":"my images eventually helped Hanifaru"},{"time":351218,"text":"become a marine-protected area."},{"time":353669,"text":"Now, fisherman from neighboring islands,"},{"time":355769,"text":"they once hunted these manta rays"},{"time":357463,"text":"to make traditional drums\nfrom their skins."},{"time":360111,"text":"Today, they are the most ardent\nconservation champions"},{"time":363810,"text":"and manta rays earn the Maldivian economy"},{"time":366111,"text":"in excess of 8 million dollars\nevery single year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":371182,"text":"I have always wanted\nto travel back in time"},{"time":373555,"text":"to an era where maps were mostly blank"},{"time":376169,"text":"or they read, \"There be dragons.\""},{"time":378122,"text":"And today, the closest I've come\nis visiting remote atolls"},{"time":381730,"text":"in the western Indian Ocean."},{"time":383446,"text":"Far, far away from shipping lanes\nand fishing fleets,"},{"time":386691,"text":"diving into these waters\nis a poignant reminder"},{"time":390049,"text":"of what our oceans once looked like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":392501,"text":"Very few people have heard\nof Bassas da India,"},{"time":395154,"text":"a tiny speck of coral\nin the Mozambique Channel."},{"time":399202,"text":"Its reef forms a protective outer barrier"},{"time":402369,"text":"and the inner lagoon is a nursery ground"},{"time":405069,"text":"for Galapagos sharks."},{"time":406608,"text":"These sharks are anything but shy,\neven during the day."},{"time":411239,"text":"I had a bit of a hunch\nthat they'd be even bolder"},{"time":413882,"text":"and more abundant at night."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416072,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":424179,"text":"Never before have I encountered"},{"time":426076,"text":"so many sharks on a single coral outcrop."},{"time":429373,"text":"Capturing and sharing moments like this --"},{"time":433480,"text":"that reminds me why I chose my path."}]},{"cues":[{"time":437488,"text":"Earlier this year, I was on assignment\nfor National Geographic Magazine"},{"time":441270,"text":"in Baja California."},{"time":442912,"text":"And about halfway down the peninsula\non the Pacific side"},{"time":445673,"text":"lies San Ignacio Lagoon,"},{"time":447136,"text":"a critical calving ground for gray whales."},{"time":449674,"text":"For 100 years, this coast was the scene\nof a wholesale slaughter,"},{"time":453964,"text":"where more than 20,000\ngray whales were killed,"},{"time":456400,"text":"leaving only a few hundred survivors."},{"time":458698,"text":"Today the descendents of these same whales"},{"time":461392,"text":"nudge their youngsters to the surface"},{"time":463279,"text":"to play and even interact with us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":467247,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":476577,"text":"This species truly has made\na remarkable comeback."}]},{"cues":[{"time":482568,"text":"Now, on the other side\nof the peninsula lies Cabo Pulmo,"},{"time":485563,"text":"a sleepy fishing village."},{"time":487260,"text":"Decades of overfishing\nhad brought them close to collapse."},{"time":490718,"text":"In 1995, local fisherman\nconvinced the authorities"},{"time":493202,"text":"to proclaim their waters a marine reserve."},{"time":495478,"text":"But what happened next\nwas nothing short of miraculous."},{"time":499055,"text":"In 2005, after only\na single decade of protection,"},{"time":503349,"text":"scientists measured the largest\nrecovery of fish ever recorded."}]},{"cues":[{"time":507866,"text":"But don't take my word\nfor it -- come with me."},{"time":510301,"text":"On a single breath, swim with me in deep,"},{"time":513063,"text":"into one of the largest\nand densest schools of fish"},{"time":516119,"text":"I have ever encountered."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519485,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":531135,"text":"We all have the ability\nto be creators of hope."},{"time":533993,"text":"And through my photography,"},{"time":535945,"text":"I want to pass on the message\nthat it is not too late for our oceans."},{"time":539432,"text":"And particularly, I want to focus\non nature's resilience"},{"time":542891,"text":"in the face of 7.3 billion people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":546901,"text":"My hope is that in the future,"},{"time":548742,"text":"I will have to search much, much harder"},{"time":550716,"text":"to make photographs like this,"},{"time":552925,"text":"while creating images that showcase"},{"time":555034,"text":"our respectful coexistence with the ocean."},{"time":558077,"text":"Those will hopefully become\nan everyday occurrence for me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":562836,"text":"To thrive and survive in my profession,"},{"time":565135,"text":"you really have to be a hopeless optimist."},{"time":568152,"text":"And I always operate on the assumption"},{"time":570197,"text":"that the next great picture\nthat will effect change"},{"time":573326,"text":"is right around the corner,"},{"time":575153,"text":"behind the next coral head,"},{"time":577510,"text":"inside the next lagoon"},{"time":579136,"text":"or possibly, in the one after it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":582673,"text":"(Music)"}]}]}